tldr: The agent reviewed the existing sleep questionnaire implementation against
  a detailed specification, identified several missing features, and then
  proceeded to implement all high and medium priority items, including a
  tiredness severity scale, COMISA detection, insufficient sleep syndrome
  detection, outbound links, weighted EDS scoring, expanded CSV export, and
  chronic fatigue screening.
overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application to ensure it met all acceptance criteria from the Statement of
  Work and a detailed questionnaire specification. The agent performed an
  in-depth analysis, identifying several critical gaps such as the absence of a
  tiredness severity scale, COMISA detection, insufficient sleep syndrome logic,
  and external resource links. The agent then proceeded to implement these and
  other medium-priority items. This involved updating data types, validation
  schemas, and modifying various UI components to capture new user inputs and
  display enhanced diagnostic information and personalized recommendations. Key
  changes included adding a weighted scoring system for daytime sleepiness,
  integrating safety warnings for severe tiredness, and expanding the data
  export functionality to include all collected questionnaire responses. The
  implementation also added new questions for pain and chronic fatigue,
  providing relevant screening and guidance in the reports.
